    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and
        Related Components - Removal - Vibration Damper, Hub, and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Vibration Damper, Hub, and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <figure id="f3350012294" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk07/K07001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Vibration damper assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 16 bolt (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 40 (12 point) damper bolt (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Damper retainer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The dowel pin for MaxxForce&#8482; 9 and 10 vibration dampers is almost flush with the damper
                    front surface. The dowel pin for MaxxForce&#8482;DT vibration dampers protrudes out approximately 6
                    mm (0.24 in).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1212" count="1">Remove six M10 x 16 bolts holding the vibration damper to the damper hub and
                remove vibration damper.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three M12 x 40 (12 point) damper bolts and remove the damper retainer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350012295" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk07/K07002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Damper hub and H-bar puller</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Damper hub</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">H-bar puller</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M10 x 80 bolts and washers through
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_299.xml" xrefid="t335001203">H-bar puller</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001203"/>
                and into the damper hub. Install M10 x 80 bolt heads at equal lengths from the vibration damper mounting
                surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten H-bar center shaft to pull damper hub off of crankshaft and remove damper hub.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350012296" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/H07027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Damper hub and wear sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Muffler chisel</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Damper hub</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not damage or distort damper hub while removing wear sleeve.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully split wear sleeve with a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_299.xml" xrefid="t335001203">muffler chisel</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001203"/>
                and remove sleeve from the damper hub. Be careful not to damage the damper hub.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
